Use One-Click Actions from Repeater Widgets

When you add an actionable dataset field to a text widget in a repeater widget, the text in the widget becomes a one-click action.

To enable one-click actions in repeater widgets, open Analytics Studio. Use the dataset editor to create a values table. Include the dataset row identifier, such as Record ID, in the list of fields. Assign an action to your chosen dataset field, such as opening a Salesforce record or invoking a Visualforce page. In the dashboard builder, configure actions for the field and column.

Then, add the dataset field to a text widget inside a repeater widget. You can now act directly from your dashboard.
title: Using One-Click Actions in Repeater Widgets
